.nh
.TH "NBFC" "1" "FEBRUARY 2026" "Notebook FanControl @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
.PP
nbfc \- Notebook FanControl client

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This program is used to control the NoteBook FanControl service.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.SS SERVICE CONTROL COMMANDS
.B nbfc
.RB { start " | " stop " | " restart " | " status " | " config " | " set " | " sensors }
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SS MISCELLANEOUS COMMANDS
.B nbfc
.RB { update " | " rate\-config " | " acpi\-dump " | " get\-model\-name " | " support " | " warranty " | " help }
.RI [ OPTIONS ]

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
.RS
Show help message and exit.
.RE

.PP
.B \-\-version
.RS
Show program's version number and exit.
.RE

.SH COMMANDS
.PP

.B start
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Start the service.

.BR \-r ", " \-\-read\-only
.RS
Start in read\-only mode.
.RE
.RE

.B stop
.RS
Stop the service.
.RE

.B restart
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Restart the service.

.BR \-r ", " \-\-read\-only
.RS
Start in read\-only mode.
.RE
.RE

.B status
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Show the service status.

.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
.RS
Show service and fan status (default).
.RE

.BR \-s ", " \-\-service
.RS
Show service status.
.RE

.BR \-f ", " \-\-fan
.I FAN INDEX
.RS
Show fan status.
.RE

.BR \-w ", " \-\-watch
.I SECONDS
.RS
Show status periodically.
.RE
.RE

.B config
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
List or apply configs.

.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
.RS
List all available configs.
.RE

.BR \-r ", " \-\-recommend
.RS
List configs which may work for your device.
.RE

.BR \-s ", " \-\-set
.I CONFIG
.RS
Set a config.
.RE

.BR \-a ", " \-\-apply
.I CONFIG
.RS
Set a config and start the service.
.RE
.RE

.B set
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Control fan speed.

.BR \-a ", " \-\-auto
.RS
Set fan speed to profile-based control.
.RE

.BR \-s ", " \-\-speed
.I PERCENT
.RS
Set fan speed to PERCENT.
.RE

.BR \-f ", " \-\-fan
.I FAN INDEX
.RS
Fan index (zero based). If not given, all available fans are set to speed.
.RE
.RE

.B sensors
.RB { list " | " set " | " show }
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Configure fan sensors.

.B list
.RS
List all available sensors and their temperature files.
.RE

.B show
.RS
Show all available fans and their sensor configuration.
.RE

.B set
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Configure which sensors are attached to a fan.

.BR \-f ", " \-\-fan
.I FAN INDEX
.RS
Specifies the fan to configure.
.RE

.BR \-s ", " \-\-sensor
.I SENSOR
.RS
Sensor to add. Can be specified multiple times.
.RE

.BR \-a ", " \-\-algorithm
.I ALGORITHM
.RS
Algorithm
.RB ( Average ", " Min ", " Max )
.RE

.B \-\-force
.RS
Force applying a sensor if it could not be found.
.RE
.RE
.RE

.B update
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Download new configuration files from the internet.

.BR \-p ", " \-\-parallel
.I NUM
.RS
Set the number of parallel downloads (default: 10).
.RE

.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
.RS
Set quiet mode.
.RE
.RE

.B rate\-config
.RI [ FILE "] [" OPTIONS ]
.RS
Rates a configuration by analyzing whether it appears safe to execute on the
current system.

.BR \-H ", " \-\-full\-help
.RS
Show help on how to interpret the results.
.RE

.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
.RS
Rate all available configuration files.
.RE

.BR \-d ", " \-\-dsdt
.I FILE
.RS
Use an alternative DSDT file.
.RE

.BR \-j ", " \-\-json
.RS
Use JSON output.
.RE

.BR \-m ", " \-\-min-score
.I SCORE
.RS
Set minimum rating threshold for displaying configurations (default: 9.0).
.RE

.BR \-n ", " \-\-no\-download
.RS
Don't download configuration rules from the repository.
.RE

.BR \-r ", " \-\-rules
.I FILE
.RS
Use an alternative rules file.
.RE

.B \-\-print\-rules
.RS
Print configuration rating rules.
.RE
.RE

.B acpi\-dump
.RB { registers " | " ec\-registers " | " methods " | " dsl }
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Dumps information of your ACPI DSDT.

.B registers
.RS
List all available registers.
.RE

.B ec\-registers
.RS
List all available embedded controller registers.
.RE

.B methods
.RS
List all available ACPI methods.
.RE

.B dsl
.RS
Disassemble your DSDT.
.RE

.BR \-f ", " \-\-file
.I FILE
.RS
Use an alternative DSDT file.
.RE

.BR \-j ", " \-\-json
.RS
Use JSON output.
.RE
.RE

.B support
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RS
Show how to support the project.

.B \-\-upload\-firmare
.RS
Upload your notebook firmware without prompting.
.RE

.B \-\-print\-command
.RS
Print command for manual firmware upload.
.RE
.RE

.B get\-model\-name
.RS
Print out the notebook's model name.
.RE

.B warranty
.RS
Show warranty.
.RE

.B help
.RS
Show help.
.RE

.SH FILES
.PP

.I @SYSCONFDIR@/nbfc/nbfc.json
.RS
The main configuration file for nbfc_service. See
.BR nbfc_service.json (5)
for further details.
.RE

.I @RUNSTATEDIR@/nbfc_service.pid
.RS
File containing the PID of current running nbfc_service.
.RE

.I @RUNSTATEDIR@/nbfc_service.socket
.RS
Socket file of nbfc_service.
.RE

.I @DATADIR@/nbfc/configs/*.json
.RS
Configuration files for various notebook models. See
.BR nbfc_service.json (5)
for further details.
.RE

.I @DATADIR@/nbfc/model_support.json
.RS
Model support database. This file maps notebook model names to configuration files.
.RE

.I /var/lib/nbfc/configs/*.json
.RS
Configuration files downloaded from the internet. Files in this directory take precedence over those in
.IR @DATADIR@/nbfc/configs .
.RE

.I /var/lib/nbfc/model_support.json
.RS
Model support database downloaded from the internet. Both
.I /var/lib/nbfc/model_support.json
and
.I @DATADIR@/nbfc/model_support.json
are taken into account.
.RE

.I /var/lib/nbfc/state.json
.RS
State file of nbfc_service. This holds the current fan speeds.
.RE

.SH EXIT STATUS
.RS
.IP 0
Everything fine
.IP 1
Generic error
.IP 2
Command-line error
.IP 3
Initialization error
.IP 5
Fatal error (memory allocation failure)
.RE

.SH BUGS
.PP
Report bugs to https://github.com/nbfc\-linux/nbfc\-linux

.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Benjamin Abendroth (braph93@gmx.de)

.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
.BR nbfc_service (1),
.BR nbfc_service.json (5),
.BR ec_probe (1),
.BR fancontrol (1)
